More about The Planet Crafter (from Steam):

From Hostile to Habitable
You are sent on an hostile planet with one mission: Make it habitable for Humans. You'll have to survive, collect resources, build your base and machines in order to heat the planet, create an atmosphere with enough oxygen and eventually geo-engineer an entire planet!

Survive, Collect, Craft
Gather minerals and resources to survive. Craft all the tools you'll need in order to fulfill your mission. Explore old crashed ships and ruins and discover a planet full of mystery.
Build you own base
You'll need a base and all sorts of machines to make yourself at home, and be able to bring life on this planet!

Key Features:
Character Thirst, Oxygen, Temperature, Health Mechanics
Base Building
Crafting
Mining ores
Build machines to create atmospheric pressure
Build machines to heat the planet
Create a biosphere with oxygen
Create life on a planet!

snippet.title: Celebrating Route 66
snippet.description:
Today‚Äôs video Doodle takes you on the ultimate American road trip, a journey along the historic Route 66. The iconic highway‚Äîknown for its retro diners, quirky motels, eclectic art installations and extraordinary landscapes‚Äîconnects Chicago, Illinois to Santa Monica, California. On this day in 1926, the name ‚ÄúU.S. 66‚Äù was first proposed for the cross-country route.

The video‚Äîset to the classic music track "Route 66" by Bobby Troup‚Äîcelebrates the cultural significance of one of America‚Äôs first national highways, and how it became a symbol of a changing nation.

snippet.title: Oscar Valdez Reflects on Loss to Shakur Stevenson, Plans to be Back
snippet.description:
Watch the post fight interview from #oscarvaldez after his loss to #shakurstevenson in the main event of #valdezstevenson. In the interview Valdez reflects on the loss and plans to return better then ever.

Next Up for Top Rank Boxing, Middleweight contender Janibek ‚ÄúQazaq Style‚Äù Alimkhanuly has been anxiously waiting for the main event spotlight, and on Saturday, May 21, he‚Äôll hope to seize it. Alimkhanuly will face undefeated Englishman Danny Dignum in a 12-round showdown for the vacant WBO Interim middleweight world title at Resorts World Event Center at Resorts World Las Vegas.

In the co-feature, former junior world champion Jamel ‚ÄúSemper Fi‚Äù Herring returns to the lightweight division in a 10-rounder against undefeated NABF titleholder Jamaine ‚ÄúThe Technician‚Äù Ortiz.
